  "topic": "European Football",
  "summary": "European Football, often referred to as soccer in the US, is a popular sport recognized worldwide. It hosts several domestic and international leagues, such as the Champions League and Europa League, featuring powerful football clubs and famous players around the globe. It's a cultural melting point and serves as an exciting sport distinct from American football. European Football, also known as soccer, is governed by the Union of European Football Associations (UEFA), and manages various leagues and competitions, attracting world-class players. It encompasses five major leagues - English Premier League, French Ligue 1, Italian Serie A, Germ...",
